Evolution of Chelle Mashura Njiva. 

Arriving: 
Brown eyed princess, born in the land of Zimbabwe. Circa 1994. Chosen daughter of a divine king in the land of Zimuto Village. Walking cows to the river. Red soil on her clothes. Dancing to the drums of her ancestors with her tribe. “ Miraculous beauty” is what they always called her as a child. Unaware of the magnitude those words held. Unaware of her power and the catalyst that was she. Moving. Changing. Hurting. Living. Loving. Growing. Flowing. Dying. Awakening. If only she knew then, that the mountains would crumble at her feet for the woman she would become. 

Becoming: 
Brown eyed goddess; diving deep into her divinity, falling in-love with the path of deep healing and becoming the highest version of herself with softness, patience, love, grace, forgiveness, compassion, discernment, and respect to her journey while fiercely loyal to her own soul. “Beauty that defies all logic, illogical beauty” is what someone called her. This time, she knew the magnitude that word carried for it enlightened God’s love within her heart allowing her to rise into her spiritual power. Beauty is her passion. 

Ascending: 
Brown eyed divine feminine; there she is. A muse. An inspiration. A soft chaos that is not disrupting but loud enough to imprint a change. A storm mixed with wind and lion. With peace and with grace. A holy woman. A sensual woman. A sacred vessel of love. In-love with the path of self mastery and vitality; multidimensionally pursuing the things that make her feel more alive. 

Soft landing: 
There is no place quite like here. May my vulnerability inspire your authenticity for every version of you was the version you needed to set you free, to get you here. If you have met me previously, erase that version of me for she no longer resides here, you’ll need to rise up to meet me again. If my expansion makes you uncomfortable, I’m ecstatic to see you go. If you have landed here, thank you for taking the time to meet me today. 

I’m Chelle “Mashura” as my grandfather used to call me which actually means “Miracle” as I’ve just recently learned & finally it all makes sense…This is the blueprint of who I am 🕊️🇿🇼

Lioness 
Heart as fierce as crashing waves. Born and taught to roar. Courage, strength, and empowerment. Here to not escape my darkness, but to love myself there. Here to be free and express my full spectrum. Here to be felt, not analyzed. To make sense of me, is to suffocate me. I am everything all at once, this is my very nature. Rising to walk with my King and rising alongside other lionesses.

“ A lioness sleeps in the heart of every woman, it’s up to you to wake her up”

Dear life

This is 29 🎉
Immense Gratitude for 28; the most transformative year I’ve had. the year of alchemizing. the year of unlearning and relearning. the year I learned what true self love is and isn’t. the year I called myself out on my own bullsh*t and the roles I played in my own suffering. the year I broke cycles that used to hold me hostage in all areas of my life. the year I began forgiving myself for accepting the bare minimum & stopped talking myself into accepting it. And most importantly, the year I truly began to believe I could, and so I did!

Hello 29, I have been preparing and am ready to align fully with all that is meant for me. May the self work I have been doing in silence continue to echo throughout every part of my life. I am at a stage in my life where settling in any way unsettles every fabric of my soul. Oh, and here is to living in a constant state of audacity…like yes, in fact I can do it. Yes, I do in fact deserve every abundant and good thing coming my way. Yes of course, all that is possible is possible for me. And yeah, I am absolutely more than fine being less palatable even if my truth doesn't taste sweet. And I am indeed going to make history. Confidently. Deliberately. Decisively. Unapologetically. What a gift it is to be alive. What a gift it is to be following God’s calling for me. What a gift. What a gift. What a gift.
